    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.13.5a"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">ENGLEWOOD CLUB.</hi>
                </fw>   
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Englewood, <hi rend="caps">N,J</hi>. Oct 7th <note type="curatorial">[1927]</note></dateline>
                
                    <salute>My dear Mr Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>By all means, use my name<add>,</add> if you wish.I think the idea a fine one and the prospectus awakens my complete sympathy, for it is true, every word of it.My wandering life as a lecturer all over the land has made me aware of of just such a situation as is limned therein, and I would try to help it in any way within my power.</p>
                <closer>                
                    <salute>Yours ever,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Richard Burton</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">5</fw>
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.13.5b"/>
                
                <note type="recipient">Richard Burton Poet &amp; Critic</note>
                
            </div1>
